      <div>
        <h3>Secure Link Token</h3>
        <div>
          <p>
            Establish communication between sites using tokens, each token has
            an auth code and the access URL for the site that created it,
            meaning that site must be accessible from the site where you apply
            the token.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a class="nav" href="/docs/overview/security.html"
          >Skupper security <span class="material-icons">chevron_right</span></a
        >
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Skupper Private Router</h3>
        <div>
          <p>
            The software running on each site that creates communication
            channels between components. You use the `skupper` CLI or native
            Kubernetes objects to configure the router for optimal component
            communication performance.
          </p>
        </div>
